::WEF Skills Disruption::According to the World Economic Forum's Future of Jobs Report 2025, what percentage of core skills do employers expect to change by 2030?{
~25% #Incorrect. The percentage is higher than 25%, reflecting more significant skills disruption anticipated over the next five years.
=39% #Correct! The WEF 2025 report found that employers expect 39% of core skills to change by 2030, reflecting the rapid pace of skills disruption in the modern workplace.
~50% #Incorrect. While skill disruption is significant, the WEF finding is 39%, not half of all core skills.
~62% #Incorrect. The WEF projects 39% skills disruption by 2030, which is substantial but not as high as 62%.
####The WEF finding that 39% of core skills will change by 2030 emphasizes the importance of developing transferable capabilities and learning agility rather than relying solely on current technical skills. This level of disruption means focusing on meta-skills that enable continuous skill acquisition.}

